edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.junicon.iterators

Class IconOperator<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.junicon.iterators.IconOperator<V>

  • public class IconOperator<V>
extends Object
    Factory methods to take functions over values into functions over IIconAtoms. The returned function over atoms invokes the user-defined closure over the dereferenced atoms to effect the operation. If no operator is defined, returns FAIL.

    IconOperator also provides support to memorize the association of a symbol to its base function over values, for separate use as a function for example using proc("+").

    The returned value of operate makes no distinction between null and an atom that holds null.

    USAGE: IconOperator.overAtoms((x,y) -> x+y).

      • overAtomsBoolean

        public static <T> BinaryOperator<IIconAtom<T>> overAtomsBoolean(BinaryOperator<T> operator)
        Create binary boolean operator over atoms from function over values. The resultant value is converted to false if not Boolean or null, otherwise true. The operator then returns the second argument if true, else fail. True or false is thus converted to succeed and fail, respectively, and if successful returns second operand.

      • overAtomsBoolean

        public static <T> UnaryOperator<IIconAtom<T>> overAtomsBoolean(UnaryOperator<T> operator)
        Create unary boolean operator over atoms from function over values. The resultant value is converted to false if not Boolean or null, otherwise true. The operator then returns the argument if true, else fail. True or false is thus converted to succeed and fail, respectively, and if successful returns second operand.
